title: Number of M & A transactions in Asia 2015 - 2017 , by country
summary: This grouped bar chart represents 9 different Quarters on X-axis for 4 groups Australia, China/Hong Kong, India, and Japan. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding SOME LABEL.
All through the Quarters, the SOME LABEL for China/Hong Kong have declined. On the other hand, for Australia the SOME LABEL have increased.
In Quarter Q4 2016, China/Hong Kong had the highest SOME LABEL 1059.0 among the 4 groups and in Q3 2017, India had the lowest SOME LABEL 156.0.
In Quarter Q4 2016, China/Hong Kong had the maximum SOME LABEL and it saw the lowest in Quarter Q2 2016 out of all 9 Quarters.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart shows SOME LABEL on the Y-axis for 9 different Quarters for 4 groups Australia, China/Hong Kong, India, and Japan that are presented on the X-axis.
All through the Quarters, the SOME LABEL for China/Hong Kong have declined. On the other hand, for Australia the SOME LABEL have increased.
Quarter Q4 2016 had the maximum SOME LABEL among all 4 groups, and it was for China/Hong Kong. The minimum SOME LABEL was observed in Quarter Q3 2017 for India.
Among all the Quarters, China/Hong Kong had the highest SOME LABEL 1059.0 in Quarter Q4 2016 and lowest value 732.0 in Quarter Q2 2016.
The maximum SOME LABEL for China/Hong Kong that was found in Quarter Q4 2016 was 1.45 times larger than the minimum SOME LABEL observed in Quarter Q2 2016.
Among all 4 groups, China/Hong Kong had the gap of 327.0 between the maximum and minimum SOME LABEL observed in Quarter Q4 2016 and Q2 2016 respectively.
China/Hong Kong had the maximum SOME LABEL out of all 4 groups in Quarter Q4 2016 followed by China/Hong Kong in Q4 2016, and the minimum SOME LABEL is found for India in Q3 2017.
On average, the Quarter Q4 2016 had the highest SOME LABEL for all 4 groups Australia, China/Hong Kong, India, and Japan. Whereas Q2 2016 had the lowest average SOME LABEL.
